    <prj:ScienceGoal>
        <prj:name>Imaging of HR4796A and search for CO as a by-product</prj:name>
        <prj:note>Goals:
- Detect the disk at 450GHz and confirm the geometry found in optical/near-IR
- Constrain the distribution of mm-sized bodies with a precision of 10AU and compare to the micrometer-sized dust from scattered light images
- Measure distorsion or azimuthal gaps in the ring 
- constrain the population of the parent bodies (planetesimals) responsible for the dust disk
- Constrain the properties of potential gravitational perturbers
- Search for gas down to a gas-to-dust ratio of 1</prj:note>
